        <h2>Maven configuration</h2>
        <p>You can configure <MadCap:variable name="General.Liquibase" /> Maven in multiple ways. You can pass arguments like <code>&lt;changeLogFile&gt;</code> in Maven <a href="../../../tools-integrations/maven/maven-properties.htm">directly in your <code>pom.xml</code> file</a>, in a <a href="../../../concepts/connections/creating-config-properties.html"><code><MadCap:variable name="General.liquiPropFile" /></code> file</a> referenced in your POM, as <a href="../../../concepts/connections/liquibase-environment-variables.htm">environment variables</a>, or as <a href="../../../concepts/connections/java-opts-environment-variable.htm">JVM system properties</a>.</p>
        <p class="tip" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;Tip: &lt;/b&gt;">For more information about the Maven configuration, see <a href="https://maven.apache.org/guides/mini/guide-configuring-maven.html">Configuring Maven</a>.</p>
